The paper discusses reinforcement learning agents and their ability to incorporate prior knowledge and reusable structure in solution space, which are topics typically covered in the machine learning and artificial intelligence sub-categories (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also focuses on continuous control tasks, which are often studied in the robotics sub-category (cs.RO). The use of hierarchical structures and their benefits for transfer learning are also discussed, which could fall under the systems and control sub-category (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions empirical results on tasks that involve visual perception, which could relate to computer vision (cs.CV).
